  "chapter": {
    "number": 40,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Humbles Himself before the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "And the LORD said to Job:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Will the faultfinder contend with the Almighty?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him who argues with God give an answer.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Then Job answered the LORD:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Behold, I am insignificant. How can I reply to You?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I place my hand over my mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have spoken once, but I have no answer—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "twice, but I have nothing to add.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The LORD Challenges Job Again"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "Then the LORD answered Job out of the whirlwind and said:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Now brace yourself",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3219
          },
          {
            "text": "like a man;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will question you, and you shall inform Me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3220
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would you really annul My justice?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Would you condemn Me to justify yourself?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you have an arm like God’s?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Can you thunder with a voice like His?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then adorn yourself with majesty and splendor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and clothe yourself with honor and glory.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Unleash the fury of your wrath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "look on every proud man and bring him low.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Look on every proud man and humble him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "trample the wicked where they stand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bury them together in the dust;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "imprison them in the grave.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3221
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I will confess to you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that your own right hand can save you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Look at Behemoth, which I made along with you.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He feeds on grass like an ox.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "See the strength of his loins",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the power in the muscles of his belly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His tail sways like a cedar;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the sinews of his thighs are tightly knit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "His bones are tubes of bronze;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his limbs are rods of iron.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He is the foremost of God’s works;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3222
          },
          {
            "text": "only his Maker can draw the sword against him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The hills yield him their produce,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while all the beasts of the field play nearby.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He lies under the lotus plants,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3223
          },
          {
            "text": "hidden among the reeds of the marsh.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The lotus plants conceal him in their shade;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the willows",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3224
          },
          {
            "text": "of the brook surround him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though the river rages, Behemoth is unafraid;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he remains secure, though the Jordan surges to his mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Can anyone capture him as he looks on,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or pierce his nose with a snare?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
